ContentDistributionEventLog.name: ContentDistributionEventLog
ContentDistributionEventLog.description: Content Distribution events contain information about content distributions and deliveries to users.

Action.description: The action that’s used when a delivery is viewed.

DeliveryIdentifier.description: The 15-character ID of the content delivery.

RelatedObjectIdentifier.description: The 15-character ID of the record that’s associated with the delivery distribution.

RequestIdentifier.description: The unique ID of a single transaction. A transaction can contain one or more events. Each event in a given transaction has the same REQUEST_ID.

Timestamp.description: The access time of Salesforce services in GMT. For example, 20130715233322.670.

UserIdentifier.description: The 15-character ID of the user who’s using Salesforce services through the UI or the API. For example: 00530000009M943.

VersionIdentifier.description: The 15-character ID of the content version.
